Create required functions.
* Calculate ACF and PACF

acf_identifier <- function(x, lags){
  # ACF
  ro <- acf(x, lag.max = lags, plot = FALSE)
  # PACF
  phi <- pacf(x, lag.max = lags, plot = FALSE)
  
  return(cbind(acf = ro$acf, pacf = phi$acf))
}
  • Identify orders
order_identifier <- function(acf_pacf, lags){
  p_hat <- 1
  q_hat <- 1

  for(l in (2:lags)){
    if(abs(acf_pacf[,'acf'][l]) > ci[2]){
      q_hat = q_hat + 1
    }
    else{
      break
    }
  }
  
  for(l in (2:lags)){
    if(abs(acf_pacf[,'pacf'][l]) > ci[2]){
      p_hat = p_hat + 1
    }
    else{
      break
    }
  }  
  return(list(p_hat = p_hat, q_hat = q_hat))
}
  • Set phi closed to 1.0. Then simulate Multiple Series AR(1) with Shared GARCH(1,1)
sim_series_large_phi <- function(u, K, n, lags, ci, eta){
  multi_series = matrix(NA, K, n)
  series_param = matrix(NA, nrow = K, ncol = 4)  
  # multiple time series share the same eta_t part
  for(k in 1:K){
    # generate different phi each time 
    # phi needs to be close to 1.0
    phi = runif(1, min = 0.7, max = 0.9)
        
    skip_to_next <- FALSE
    
    series_param[k,1] = u
    
    # the values of AR coefficients (ARIMA)
    series_param[k,2] = phi
    
    possibleError <- tryCatch({
      # use shared eta to simulate a AR(u) model
      multi_series[k,] = arima.sim(list(ar = phi), n, innov = eta$garch)
      
      # ACF
      series_ro <- pacf(multi_series[k,], lag.max = lags, plot = FALSE)
      series_param[k,3] <- sum(abs(series_ro$acf) > ci[2])
      series_param[k,4] <- 1    
      }, 
      error = function(e) {
        e
        print(paste("Skip the non-stationary series in loop ",k,sep = ""))
        })
    
    if(inherits(possibleError, "error")) next
  }
  results <- list(series = multi_series, params = series_param)
  return(results)  
}
  • Set phi closed to 0.0. Then simulate Multiple Series AR(1) with Shared GARCH(1,1)
sim_series_small_phi <- function(u, K, n, lags, ci, eta){
  multi_series = matrix(NA, K, n)
  series_param = matrix(NA, nrow = K, ncol = 4)  
  # multiple time series share the same eta_t part
  for(k in 1:K){
    # generate different phi each time 
    # phi needs to be close to 1.0
    phi = runif(1, min = 0.01, max = 0.05)
        
    skip_to_next <- FALSE
    
    series_param[k,1] = u
    
    # the values of AR coefficients (ARIMA)
    series_param[k,2] = phi
    
    possibleError <- tryCatch({
      # use shared eta to simulate a AR(u) model
      multi_series[k,] = arima.sim(list(ar = phi), n, innov = eta$garch)
      
      # ACF
      series_ro <- pacf(multi_series[k,], lag.max = lags, plot = FALSE)
      series_param[k,3] <- sum(abs(series_ro$acf) > ci[2])
      series_param[k,4] <- 1    
      }, 
      error = function(e) {
        e
        print(paste("Skip the non-stationary series in loop ",k,sep = ""))
        })
    
    if(inherits(possibleError, "error")) next
  }
  results <- list(series = multi_series, params = series_param)
  return(results)  
}
  • Create a function to estimate AR orders and get residuals
ar_estimator <- function(series, K, N, lags){

acfs <- matrix(NA, ncol = 2, nrow = lags, dimnames = list(NULL,c('acf','pacf')))
orders <- matrix(NA, ncol = 2, nrow = N, dimnames = list(NULL,c('p_hat','q_hat')))
residuals_matrix <- matrix(NA, ncol = n, nrow = N)
phis <- matrix(NA, ncol = 1, nrow = N)
results <- list(NA)

  for(index in (1:N)){
    tar_ts <- series[index,]
    
    # ACF
    ro <- acf(tar_ts, lag.max = lags, plot = FALSE)
    # PACF
    phi <- pacf(tar_ts, lag.max = lags, plot = FALSE)
    
    acfs[,'acf'] <- as.vector(ro$acf)
    acfs[,'pacf'] <- as.vector(phi$acf)
    arma_orders <- order_identifier(acfs, lags)  
    orders[index,] <- c(arma_orders$p_hat, arma_orders$q_hat)
    
    # assumption: series has AR component
    fit_ts = arima(tar_ts, order = c(arma_orders$p_hat,0,0), method = c("ML"))
    x = fit_ts$residuals  
    residuals_matrix[index,] <- x
    phis[index,] <- fit_ts$coef[1]
  }
  results <- list(orders = orders, residuals = residuals_matrix, phi = phis)
  return(results) 
}

Firstly, we need to initialize hyperparameters:

u = 1 # AR order
v = 0 # MA order
p = 1 # GARCH order
q = 1 # GARCH order

Setup fixed values of parameters

mu = 0 # (the linear part) the mean value, by default NULL
omega = 0.01 # the constant coefficient of the variance equation (default 1e-6)
alpha = 0.2
beta = 0.5
lags = 20

# length of time series
n = 300

Simulate Multiple Time Series AR(1)+GARCH(1,1)

  • Fixed order \(u = 1\)
  • Fixed order \(p = 1, q = 1\)
# n = 300
K = 200  # simulate 200 time series
acf_matrix <- matrix(NA, ncol = 2, nrow = lags, dimnames = list(NULL,c('acf','pacf')))
# confidence interval
ci = c(-1.96/sqrt(n), 1.96/sqrt(n))
# GARCH(1,1)
spec = garchSpec(model = list(mu = mu, omega = omega, alpha = alpha, beta = beta), cond.dist = "norm")
# get the true eta
eta = garchSim(spec, n)
# get the true sigma
fitted.true <- garchFit(~ garch(1,1), 
                        data=eta,
                        cond.dist="norm",
                        include.mean = FALSE,
                        trace = FALSE)

Calculate Weights Using Phi

# all actual phi values
phi.true <- cbind(res.small$params[,2], res.large$params[,2])
# all estimated phi values
phi.est1 <- cbind(est_res.small$phi, est_res.large$phi)

Calculate weight values

# w0 = 1/phi
w0 <- 1/phi.est1
# w = w0/sum(w0)
w <- w0/(sum(rowSums(w0)))

Calculate shared GARCH components with weights

# weights
#w <- c(w)
# all residuals
est_residual <- rbind(est_res.small$residuals, est_res.large$residuals)
# calculate estimated eta
eta_hat <- c(w)%*%est_residual

Estimate GARCH orders

x <- c(eta_hat)
# ACF and PACF
arch_identify <- acf_identifier(x, lags)
garch_orders_hat <- order_identifier(arch_identify, lags)

if(AIC_1 < AIC_2){
  fitted.residual <- fitted.res1

  fitted.residual <- fitted.res2
}

Check Residuals of GARCH (epsilon_t)

Look at Q-Q Plot of residuals of GARCH model, which is \(\epsilon_t = \eta_t/sqrt(garchFit)\) = Residuals/sqrt(Conditional variance). We can compute it directly from R, and plot the Q-Q graph to check the normality of the residuals.

#garch_res = est_residual / fitted.residual@sigma.t
garch_res = eta_hat / fitted.residual@sigma.t
#garch_res = residuals(fitted.residual, standardize=TRUE)

Followings are the codes and Q-Q plot.

garch_res <- as.matrix(garch_res)
qqnorm(garch_res, main='GARCH Standard Residuals')
qqline(colMeans(garch_res))

hist(garch_res, prob = TRUE, breaks = 60, 
     main = "GARCH Standard Residuals Density", xlab="Residuals") # Density
xlab <- seq(min(garch_res), max(garch_res))
ylab <- dnorm(xlab, mean = mean(garch_res), sd = sd(garch_res))
lines(xlab, ylab, col = "red", lwd = 2)
